FBIS4-65982 "drweu102_q_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-102 Daily Report 25 May 1994 TURKEY Government Welcomes UN Package on Straits Traffic Government Welcomes UN Package on Straits Traffic TA2505184794 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 GMT 25 May 94 TA2505184794 Ankara TRT Television Network Turkish BFN [Announcer-read report] [Text] Turkey has welcomed the fact that the UN International Maritime Organization accepted the package of rules and proposals to enhance the safety of passages through the Istanbul and Canakkale Straits. A Foreign Ministry statement noted that regulating the traffic in the straits will benefit all interested parties. The statement remarked that the new statute pertaining to the passage through the straits was prepared in line with basic international rules of law, which stipulate that every country can determine the procedures in the waters under its own sovereignty in order to ensure maritime safety and environmental protection. This statute will go into effect on 1 July 1994, the statement noted, adding that the new statute will continue to adhere meticulously to the Montreux Convention, as was the case in the past.
